# Module Creation Guide

## Creating a New Module

When creating a new module, follow this step-by-step process:

### 1. Create Module Structure
```bash
mkdir -p src/modules/{module-name}/{domain,application,infrastructure}/{entities,repositories,mappers,events,enums,use-cases,services,dto,exceptions,controllers,persistence,event-handlers}
```

### 2. Create Module Files

#### `{module-name}.module.ts`
```typescript
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';

@Module({
  imports: [],
  providers: [
    // Use cases with DI tokens
    // Domain mappers
    // Repository implementations
    // Services
    // Event handlers
  ],
  controllers: [],
  exports: [], // Export what other modules need
})
export class {ModuleName}Module {}
```

#### `constants.ts`
```typescript
export const {ModuleName}DiToken = {
  // Use case tokens
  CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE: Symbol('CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE'),
  
  // Repository tokens
  {ENTITY}_REPOSITORY: Symbol('{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY'),
  
  // Service tokens
  {ENTITY}_SERVICE: Symbol('{ENTITY}_SERVICE'),
} as const;
```

### 3. Create Domain Layer

#### Entity (`domain/entities/{entity}.entity.ts`)
```typescript
import { Builder } from 'builder-pattern';

export class {Entity} {
  public readonly id: string;
  // Define properties
  
  public static builder() {
    return Builder({Entity}, {
      // Default values
    });
  }
}
```

#### Repository Interface (`domain/repositories/{entity}-repository.interface.ts`)
```typescript
export interface I{Entity}Repository {
  create(entity: {Entity}): Promise<{Entity}>;
  findById(id: string): Promise<{Entity} | null>;
  // Define other methods
}
```

#### Mapper (`domain/mappers/{entity}/{entity}.mapper.ts`)
```typescript
export class {Entity}Mapper {
  toDomain(raw: any): {Entity} {
    // Map from persistence to domain
  }
  
  toPersistence(entity: {Entity}): any {
    // Map from domain to persistence
  }
}
```

### 4. Create Application Layer

#### Use Case (`application/use-cases/{operation}/{operation}.use-case.ts`)
```typescript
import { Inject, Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';
import { Command } from '~shared/application/CQS/command.abstract';

@Injectable()
export class {Operation}UseCase extends Command<{InputDto}, {OutputType}> implements I{Operation}UseCase {
  constructor(
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY)
    private readonly {entity}Repository: I{Entity}Repository,
  ) {
    super();
  }

  protected async implementation(): Promise<{OutputType}> {
    // Business logic implementation
  }
}
```

#### DTO (`application/dto/{operation}.dto.ts`)
```typescript
import { IsString, IsOptional } from 'class-validator';

export class {Operation}Dto {
  @IsString()
  name: string;
  
  @IsOptional()
  @IsString()
  description?: string;
}
```

### 5. Create Infrastructure Layer

#### Controller (`infrastructure/controllers/{entity}/{entity}.controller.ts`)
```typescript
import { Controller, Post, Body, UseGuards } from '@nestjs/common';
import { ApiTags, ApiOperation } from '@nestjs/swagger';

@ApiTags('{entity}')
@Controller('{entity}')
export class {Entity}Controller {
  constructor(
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE)
    private readonly create{Entity}UseCase: ICreate{Entity}UseCase,
  ) {}

  @Post()
  @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Create {entity}' })
  async create(@Body() dto: Create{Entity}Dto): Promise<{Entity}> {
    return this.create{Entity}UseCase.execute(dto);
  }
}
```

#### Repository Implementation (`infrastructure/persistence/drizzle/repositories/drizzle-{entity}.repository.ts`)
```typescript
import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';
import { I{Entity}Repository } from '~modules/{module-name}/domain/repositories/{entity}-repository.interface';

@Injectable()
export class Drizzle{Entity}Repository implements I{Entity}Repository {
  async create(entity: {Entity}): Promise<{Entity}> {
    // Database implementation
  }
}
```

### 6. Register in App Module
```typescript
// src/app.module.ts
import { {ModuleName}Module } from '~modules/{module-name}/{module-name}.module';

@Module({
  imports: [
    // ... other modules
    {ModuleName}Module,
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Naming Convention**: Use PascalCase for classes, camelCase for methods/properties
2. **Dependency Injection**: Always use DI tokens from constants.ts
3. **Error Handling**: Extend base exception classes from core module
4. **Validation**: Use class-validator decorators in DTOs
5. **Testing**: Create unit tests for use cases and integration tests for controllers
6. **Documentation**: Use Swagger decorators for API documentation
